The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Centurion Bank profit leaps 251%

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, July 11: Centurion Bank has reported a 251 per cent rise in its standalone net profit for the first quarter of the current fiscal at Rs 11.1 crore compared with Rs 3.2 crore in the year-ago period.

 Net retail advances grew 67 per cent to Rs 2319.6 crore from Rs 1392.7 crore in the corresponding period last year. Of this, the two-wheeler financing business contributed the largest chunk of Rs 1016.8 crore followed by commercial vehicles financing at Rs 818.5 crore, personal loans at Rs 185.5 crore, mortgages at Rs 43l.6 crore and others at Rs 255.2 crore.

 The banks interest earnings increased 16.6 per cent to Rs 99.3 crore from Rs 85.1 crore. However, the banks net interest margin slumped to 5.3 per cent from 5.7 per cent.

 Net non-performing assets came down to 2.4 per cent from 4.4 per cent.

 Managing director Shailendra Bhandari said, The banks standalone results show a consistent trend of growth and improvement in profitability. We expect to strengthen further after the merger with the Bank of Punjab.




